+> **Scoring note — custom helpers vs strong signals**: A helper registered in `custom_helper_registry` may also appear in `file.signals.strong[]` if ToolA promoted it during scanning. To avoid double-counting, `find_signal_in_pattern` must use a single unified lookup: if the helper name exists in `strong_signals`, it contributes via the custom helpers block above — ToolA will **not** also list it under `signals.strong[]` with a separate `occurrences` entry for the same call-sites. However, implementors should add a guard: if a name appears in both `signals.strong` and `custom_helpers_called`, count it only once (via the strong signals loop; skip it in the custom helpers loop).
